'''2016年共和党全国代表大会'''于2016年7月18日至21日在[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]][[克利夫兰_(俄亥俄州)|克利夫兰]]的[[快贷球馆|快贷球馆]]举行<ref name="RNC">[http://www.cbsnews.com/news/rnc-officially-approves-cleveland-as-2016-convention-host/ "RNC officially approves Cleveland as 2016 convention host"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/rnc-officially-approves-cleveland-as-2016-convention-host/ |date=20160629222454 }}, [[CBS新聞|CBS News]].</ref>，会上[[美國|美國]][[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]]的代表选出代表该党参选[[2016年美国总统选举|2016年美国总统选举]]的[[美国总统|总统]]和[[美国副总统|副总统]]的候选人。这是克利夫兰第三次主办这项活动，且是自1936年来的第一次<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2014/07/08/cleveland-to-hold-2016-republican-convention/|title=Cleveland to hold 2016 Republican convention|accessdate=2014-07-08|date=2014-07-08|publisher=[[CNN.com|CNN.com]]|author1=Preston, Mark|author2=Steinhauser, Paul|archive-date=2016-06-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601202254/http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2014/07/08/cleveland-to-hold-2016-republican-convention/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。除了决定党的全国候选人名单外，该大会也将批准党的[[政纲|政纲]]。

共和党全国代表大会有2,472名代表，候选人需要得到简单多数也就是1,237或更多的代表支持以取得总统候选人的资格<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/things-delegates-stake-iowa-caucuses-36634904|title=Things to Know About Delegates at Stake in Iowa Caucuses|accessdate=2016-02-02|publisher=ABC|last1=Ohlemacher|first1=Stephen|website=ABC News|archive-date=2016-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202022954/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/things-delegates-stake-iowa-caucuses-36634904|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thegreenpapers.com/P16/|title=Election 2016:  Presidential Primaries, Caucuses, and Conventions|date=2016-02-10|publisher=Green Papers|accessdate=2016-07-08|archive-date=2016-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707070105/http://www.thegreenpapers.com/P16/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。大多数的代表将至少在第一轮投票时受到[[2016年美國總統選舉共和黨初選|初选]]结果的约束。党代会最终提名[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]和[[迈克·彭斯|迈克·彭斯]]分别作为总统和副总统候选人<ref>{{cite web|last1=Anderson|first1=Meg|title=RECAP: A Round-Up Of Can't-Miss Stories From The RNC|url=http://www.npr.org/2016/07/23/487048891/recap-a-round-up-of-cant-miss-stories-from-the-rnc|publisher=NPR|accessdate=2016-07-25|archive-date=2016-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809050033/http://www.npr.org/2016/07/23/487048891/recap-a-round-up-of-cant-miss-stories-from-the-rnc|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 背景 ==
民主党和共和党都将2016年的党代表大会定于七月底，在[[2016年夏季奥林匹克运动会|奥运会]]之前举行，而非如2008年和2012年般在奥运会之后举行。[[CNN|CNN]]报道称，共和党将其党代表大会定于七月举行的原因是避免发生{{link-en|2012年美国共和党总统初选|Republican Party presidential primaries, 2012|如2012年}}般冗长的初选，并留出更多时间让整个党团结在候选人周围。根据CNN报道，[[共和党全国委员会|共和党全国委员会]]还考虑过在六月举行党代会。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/01/14/politics/rnc-sets-2016-presidential-convention-date/index.html |title=First on CNN: RNC sets 2016 presidential convention date |date=2015-01-15 |accessdate=2016-08-04 |author=Mark Preston |publisher=CNN |quote=Moving the convention to July is just one of several moves by Priebus to try and put the GOP nominee in the strongest possible position heading into the 2016 general election. Naming a nominee in July will give the party more time to rally behind the candidate. And Priebus is also working to limit the number of primary debates and is condensing the primary calendar to avoid a long, drawn out battle for the GOP nomination.The RNC had also considered holding the convention in June before deciding on the July date. |archive-date=2016-07-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160731073505/http://www.cnn.com/2015/01/14/politics/rnc-sets-2016-presidential-convention-date/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>民主党则紧随其后，将其党代表大会定于共和党党代表大会一个星期后举行，以做出更快的应对。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/01/23/politics/democratic-national-convention-date-set/|title=Democratic National Convention date set|accessdate=2015-08-25|date=2015-01-23|last=Jaffe|first=Alexandra|publisher=CNN|quote=The July date is two months earlier than Democrats' 2012 convention, but it sets the Democrats up to immediately follow the GOP's festivities ... Republicans moved their convention back a month in hopes of avoiding the drawn-out primary battle that left the party fractured and their 2012 nominee wounded heading into the general election|archive-date=2016-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160709151252/http://www.cnn.com/2015/01/23/politics/democratic-national-convention-date-set|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2016年5月3日，德克萨斯州众议员[[泰德·克鲁兹|泰德·克鲁兹]]宣布終止競選活動（退选）后，共和党全国委员会主席[[赖因斯·普里巴斯|赖因斯·普里巴斯]]宣布商人[[唐纳德·川普|唐纳德·川普]]为共和党假定提名的總統候選人（實際上勝出總統初選）。次日，俄亥俄州州长[[约翰·凯西克|约翰·凯西克]]宣布退选，更加巩固特朗普假定提名人地位。特朗普是继1940年共和党总统候选人[[温德尔·威尔基|温德尔·威尔基]]后第一个在获提名前没有担任过政府官员或在军队中任职的主要政党总统候选人，也是继1952年共和党总统候选人[[德怀特·艾森豪威尔|德怀特·艾森豪威尔]]上将后第一个没有从政经验的主要政党总统候选人。

这是自1980年第一次完全于7月进行的共和党全国代表。

=== 申办流程 ===
2014年4月2日，共和党全国委员会宣布2016年党代会候选城市为[[辛辛那提_(俄亥俄州)|辛辛那提]]、[[克利夫兰_(俄亥俄州)|克利夫兰]]、[[达拉斯|达拉斯]]、[[丹佛|丹佛]]、[[堪萨斯城_(密苏里州)|堪萨斯城]]和[[拉斯维加斯|拉斯维加斯]]<ref>(April 2, 2014) [http://www.thedenverchannel.com/news/local-news/denver-hoping-to-make-next-2016-republican-national-convention-rnc-cut "Denver makes latest cut for hosting 2016 Republican National Convention (RNC)."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.thedenverchannel.com/news/local-news/denver-hoping-to-make-next-2016-republican-national-convention-rnc-cut |date=20140406090138 }}</ref>。6月下旬，克利夫兰和达拉斯成为最终候选的两座城市<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chronicle.northcoastnow.com/national-news/2014/06/25/UPDATED-Cleveland-Dallas-finalists-to-host-2016-Republican-National-Convention.html |title=Cleveland, Dallas finalists to host 2016 Republican National Convention |work=The Chronicle |location=Lorain County, Ohio |agency=Associated Press |date=2014-06-25 |accessdate=2016-08-04 |archive-date=2016-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818114716/http://chronicle.northcoastnow.com/national-news/2014/06/25/UPDATED-Cleveland-Dallas-finalists-to-host-2016-Republican-National-Convention.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。7月8日，克利夫兰当选为主办城市<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/govbeat/wp/2014/07/08/republicans-choose-cleveland-for-2016-convention/|title=Republicans choose Cleveland for 2016 convention|last=Wilson|first=Reid|date=2014-07-08|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|access-date=2016-07-12|archive-date=2016-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822073411/https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/govbeat/wp/2014/07/08/republicans-choose-cleveland-for-2016-convention/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 主办机构 ===
位于俄亥俄州的非营利无附属政治机构的2016克利夫兰主办委员会（{{lang|en|The 2016 Cleveland Host Committee}}）是这次党代会的官方和联邦指定主办机构，其职责是“推进俄亥俄东北部以及克利夫兰更具代表性，及在举办2016年共和党代表大会期间减轻地方政府压力”<ref name="host">{{cite web|url=https://www.2016cle.com/the-host-committee|title=The Host Committee|work=Cleveland 2016 Host Committee, Inc.|accessdate=2016-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116141628/https://www.2016cle.com/the-host-committee|archive-date=2016-11-16|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。委员会成员由俄亥俄州的知名商界人士、公民领袖和其他社区领袖组成<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cleveland.com/business/index.ssf/2015/03/downtown_cleveland_could_vault_into_the_major_leagues_after_the_rnc_2016_city_club_panelists_say.html#incart_related_stories|title=Cleveland could vault into major leagues after hosting 2016 Republican National Convention, City Club panelists say (photos)|work=The Plain Dealer|accessdate=2016-08-04|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304080938/http://www.cleveland.com/business/index.ssf/2015/03/downtown_cleveland_could_vault_into_the_major_leagues_after_the_rnc_2016_city_club_panelists_say.html#incart_related_stories|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cleveland.com/metro/index.ssf/2015/03/2016_republican_national_conve_1.html|title=2016 Republican National Convention in Cleveland is a 'free-market economy' for event spaces|work=The Plain Dealer|accessdate=2016-08-04|archive-date=2016-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160514222401/http://www.cleveland.com/metro/index.ssf/2015/03/2016_republican_national_conve_1.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，委员会主席为大卫·吉尔伯特<ref name = "host" />。大会筹办过程中，组委会发现筹钱有些困难。钱款一般来自企业捐款，而一些企业给2012年党代会捐款上十万美元却没有为2016年党代会出钱，包括[[摩根大通|摩根大通]]、[[通用电气|通用电气]]、[[福特汽车公司|福特汽车公司]]、[[摩托罗拉解决方案|摩托罗拉解决方案]]和[[安进|安进]]。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnbc.com/2016/07/12/corporations-slash-republican-convention-funding.html|title=Corporations slash Republican convention funding|last=Levingston|first=Ivan|date=2016-07-12|publisher=CNBC|accessdate=2016-07-17|archive-date=2016-08-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160807063632/http://www.cnbc.com/2016/07/12/corporations-slash-republican-convention-funding.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>其中一些企业没有出钱的因素包括不愿与特朗普扯上关系以及担心会场内发生暴力冲突<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2016/06/apple-wont-aid-gop-convention-over-trump-224513|title=Apple won't aid GOP convention over Trump|last=Romm|first=Tony|date=2016-06-18|work=Politico|accessdate=2016-07-17|archive-date=2016-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160804210748/http://www.politico.com/story/2016/06/apple-wont-aid-gop-convention-over-trump-224513|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/31/us/politics/donald-trump-republican-national-convention.html|title=Corporations Grow Nervous About Participating in Republican Convention|last1=Martin|first1=Jonathan|last2=Haberman|first2=Maggie|date=2016-03-30|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2016-07-17|archive-date=2016-07-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160725190237/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/31/us/politics/donald-trump-republican-national-convention.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年7月党代会开始后，组委会宣布已筹得其6400万美元筹款目标中的5800万，并寻求屡次给共和党出钱的富翁[[谢尔登·阿德尔森|谢尔登·阿德尔森]]弥补剩下的600万美元缺口<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2016-election/convention-planners-sought-6-million-sheldon-adelson-n610476|title=GOP Convention Planners Sought $6 Million From Sheldon Adelson|last=Caldwell|first=Leigh Ann|date=2016-07-15|publisher=NBC News|accessdate=2016-07-17|archive-date=2016-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160805194236/http://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2016-election/convention-planners-sought-6-million-sheldon-adelson-n610476|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 安全安排和规划 ===
本次党代会是[[美国国土安全部|美国国土安全部]]指定的{{link-en|国家安全特别事件|National Special Security Event}}，这意味着{{link-en|执法|Law enforcement}}方的层级可至[[美国特勤局|特勤局]]和国土安全部<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/23/us/politics/to-prepare-for-convention-tampa-restricts-protests.html To Prepare for Republican Convention, Tampa Restricts Protests] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/23/us/politics/to-prepare-for-convention-tampa-restricts-protests.html |date=20161105064434 }}. ''[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]''. July 22, 2012</ref>。会前，一份要求在大会举办地快贷球馆允许[[美国公开持武权|公开持枪]]的{{link-en|网上请愿|Online petition|网络倡议}}得到45000份签名<ref name="WKYC">{{cite web|url=http://www.wkyc.com/news/politics/rnc/cleveland-police-union-naacp-have-rnc-security-concerns/106659555|title=Cleveland police union, NAACP have RNC security concerns|first=Tom|last=Beres|call-sign=[[WKYC|WKYC]]|language=en-US|date=2016-03-28|access-date=2016-08-04|archive-date=2016-08-04|archive-url=https://archive.today/20160804132621/http://www.wkyc.com/news/politics/rnc/cleveland-police-union-naacp-have-rnc-security-concerns/106659555}}</ref>，不过，负责大会安保事宜的特勤局宣布不允许携带枪支进入场馆内<ref>Niraj Chokshi, [https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/03/28/more-than-42000-people-have-signed-a-petition-to-allow-guns-at-the-republican-national-convention/ Secret Service: We're not allowing firearms at the Republican National Convention] {{Wayback|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/03/28/more-than-42000-people-have-signed-a-petition-to-allow-guns-at-the-republican-national-convention/ |date=20160811000913 }}, ''The Washington Post'' (March 28, 2016).</ref>以及紧挨场馆的“安全区域”<ref name="KriegSuspension">Gregory Krieg, [http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/17/politics/cleveland-police-baton-rouge-security-open-carry/ Cleveland police union asks for suspension of 'open carry' in wake of Baton Rouge, ahead of RNC] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/17/politics/cleveland-police-baton-rouge-security-open-carry/ |date=20160809002556 }}, CNN (July 17, 2016).</ref>。特勤局于2016年5月下旬发表的一份声明称：“携带枪支的个人不允许通过指定位置的外围安检口，不论其是否持有参加大会的票证。”<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chiacu|first1=Doina|title=Secret Service says 'no' to guns at Republican convention|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-election-guns-idUSKCN0WU1PE|agency=Reuters|accessdate=2016-03-28|archive-date=2016-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160813153413/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-election-guns-idUSKCN0WU1PE|dead-url=no}}</ref>根据有关规定，特勤局有权在需要保护特定个人的场所限制枪支及其他武器<ref>{{cite web|last1=Faulders|first1=Katherine|title=Secret Service Will Not Allow Guns at GOP Convention Despite Petition for Open Carry|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/secret-service-guns-gop-convention-petition-open-carry/story?id=37981517|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=2016-03-28|archive-date=2016-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160720081727/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/secret-service-guns-gop-convention-petition-open-carry/story?id=37981517|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

{{link-en|克利夫兰警察局|Cleveland Division of Police}}获得了5000万美元的联邦补助金来进行警务活动<ref>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Kate |title=Cities Bill Trump for the High Cost of Rallies |url=http://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2016-06-30/trump-rallies |accessdate=2016-07-10 |publisher=[[Bloomberg_L.P.|Bloomberg L.P.]] |date=2016-06-30 |archive-date=2016-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806185631/http://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2016-06-30/trump-rallies |dead-url=no }}</ref>，其中2000万用于购买了超过2000套[[防暴|防暴]]警员装备，剩余3000万会则用于人事方面<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cleveland.com/rnc-2016/index.ssf/2016/03/cleveland_seeking_to_buy_riot.html|title=Cleveland seeking to buy riot gear for Republican National Convention|work=The Plain Dealer|accessdate=2016-04-15|archive-date=2016-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160727050325/http://www.cleveland.com/rnc-2016/index.ssf/2016/03/cleveland_seeking_to_buy_riot.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。克利夫兰当局在紧挨大会举办场馆的约440万平方米（1.7平方英里）“安全区域”禁止[[水枪|水枪]]、剑、[[网球|网球]]和保温壶，但根据{{link-en|俄亥俄州枪支法|Gun laws in Ohio|俄亥俄州一份允许公开持枪的法律}}，此区域允许持枪<ref name="KriegSuspension"/><ref>Mary Kilpatrick, [http://www.cleveland.com/open/index.ssf/2016/06/guns_allowed_water_guns_banned.html Guns allowed, water guns banned in the Republican National Convention event zone: Here's why] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cleveland.com/open/index.ssf/2016/06/guns_allowed_water_guns_banned.html |date=20160807122333 }}, ''[[The_Plain_Dealer|The Plain Dealer]]'' (June 1, 2016).</ref><ref>Laura Bult, [http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/water-guns-banned-rnc-firearms-won-article-1.2695913 Water guns will be banned at Cleveland's Republican National Convention — firearms won't be] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/water-guns-banned-rnc-firearms-won-article-1.2695913 |date=20160817134037 }}, ''Daily News'' (New York) (July 1, 2016).</ref><ref>Eliza Collins, [http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2016/07/14/rnc-convention-banned-items/87074530/ Tennis balls, coolers, lasers: What's been banned at the RNC] {{Wayback|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2016/07/14/rnc-convention-banned-items/87074530/ |date=20160724164712 }}, ''USA Today'' (July 14, 2016).</ref>。[[美国全国有色人种协进会|美国全国有色人种协进会]]克利夫兰分支机构于2016年3月致信市郡领导对大会安全表示担忧，称警察没有准备好应对“可能出现的挥舞枪支的抗议示威者”<ref name="WKYC"/><ref>{{cite web|first=Bill|last=Sheil|url=http://fox8.com/2016/03/28/naacp-expresses-concern-over-rnc-security/|title=NAACP expresses concern over RNC security|call-sign=[[WJW_(TV)|WJW]]|date=2016-03-30|accessdate=2016-08-04|archive-date=2016-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821004946/http://fox8.com/2016/03/28/naacp-expresses-concern-over-rnc-security/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。克利夫兰市警察工会也表达了类似的担忧，称警察的训练和装备配备方面都没有跟上进度<ref name="WKYC"/>。7月16日，大会开始前一天，市警察工会要求俄亥俄州州长约翰·凯西克暂停该州的公开持枪法，以阻止在大会区域持枪，但遭到凯西克拒绝。他表示：“俄亥俄州的州长无权根据这个建议，武断地暂停联邦和州的宪法赋予的权利或州的法律”。<ref name="KriegSuspension"/>

大会开始前，网上出现了一些[[钓鱼式攻击|钓鱼式攻击]]团伙，可能是黑客试图在会场网络中寻找漏洞<ref>[https://www.yahoo.com/tech/why-hackers-targeting-gop-convention-000000310.html Why hackers are targeting the GOP convention] {{Wayback|url=https://www.yahoo.com/tech/why-hackers-targeting-gop-convention-000000310.html |date=20160713214803 }}, by Rick Newman, on Yahoo!Tech, July 12, 2016.</ref>。此前，民主党全国委员会的网络系统已经被可能与俄罗斯有联系的黑客攻击，泄露出针对特朗普做的对手调查<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/russian-government-hackers-penetrated-dnc-stole-opposition-research-on-trump/2016/06/14/cf006cb4-316e-11e6-8ff7-7b6c1998b7a0_story.html Russian government hackers penetrated DNC, stole opposition research on Trump] {{Wayback|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/russian-government-hackers-penetrated-dnc-stole-opposition-research-on-trump/2016/06/14/cf006cb4-316e-11e6-8ff7-7b6c1998b7a0_story.html |date=20190522235639 }}, by Ellen Nakashima, in ''The Washington Post'', June 14, 2016.</ref>。2016年7月17日，《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》报道称：“克利夫兰已特别派遣约500名警员处理大会安保，并从远到加利福尼亚和得克萨斯的警察局调来上千名警员来协助”<ref>Alexander Burns, [http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/18/us/politics/trump-rnc-baton-rogue.html On Eve of the Republican Convention, Law and Order Takes the Floor] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/18/us/politics/trump-rnc-baton-rogue.html |date=20160724085739 }}, ''The New York Times'' (July 17, 2016).</ref>。

=== 抗议计划 ===
《[[洛杉矶时报|洛杉矶时报]]》2016年3月的一篇文章认为大会现场恐将出现动荡不稳的局面，原因包括“（举办）城市曾发生饱受争议的警察开枪事件和种族间的紧张对立；候选人（特朗普）声称如果他获得代表票数最多却不能拿到提名的话，他的支持者会暴动；以及警方有着滥用暴力的坏名声”。<ref name="LATimes">{{cite web|first=Matt|last=Pearce|url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-republican-convention-protests-20160321-story.html|title=This summer's Republican convention protests will be fueled by a volatile mix of forces|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=2016-03-30|accessdate=2016-08-07|archive-date=2016-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814041910/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-republican-convention-protests-20160321-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>特别是克利夫兰曾发生警察枪杀平民的[[塔米尔·莱斯枪杀案|塔米尔·莱斯枪杀案]]和[[蒂莫西·罗素和马丽萨·威廉姆斯枪杀案|蒂莫西·罗素和马丽萨·威廉姆斯枪杀案]]，而且2014年[[美国司法部|司法部]]一份调查曾批评克利夫兰警察习惯性运用“不合理且不必要的武力”，因而克利夫兰警察局被质疑是否有管控抗议的能力<ref name="LATimes"/>。自从本次大会消息最早于2014年公布开始，左翼人士便一直计划抗议行动<ref name="LATimes"/>。到5月19日时，六个组织已经提交抗议活动许可申请，但还没有一个通过。克利夫兰当局甚至公开了申请资料，希望借此拖延时间，而[[2016年民主党全国代表大会|民主党代表大会]]举办地[[费城|费城]]当局已经批准了一个抗议活动<ref>Mark Naymik, [http://www.cleveland.com/naymik/index.ssf/2016/05/cleveland_stalling_rnc_protest.html Philadelphia approves first DNC protest application while Cleveland continues to stall on RNC requests] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cleveland.com/naymik/index.ssf/2016/05/cleveland_stalling_rnc_protest.html |date=20160802084715 }}, ''The Plain Dealer'' (May 13, 2016).</ref>。第二天，又有一些组织递交了抗议活动申请，包括{{link-en|艾滋病保健基金会|AIDS Healthcare Foundation}}、{{link-en|全球零核|Global Zero (campaign)}}等<ref name="TobiasGroupsFile">{{cite news|last1=Tobias|first1=Andres|title=Three additional groups, including two anti-Trump groups, file for Cleveland protest permits during Republican National Convention|url=http://www.cleveland.com/rnc-2016/index.ssf/2016/05/three_additional_groups_includ.html|work=The Plain Dealer|date=2016-05-20|accessdate=2016-08-07|archive-date=2016-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160726102505/http://www.cleveland.com/rnc-2016/index.ssf/2016/05/three_additional_groups_includ.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年5月，[[美国公民自由联盟|美国公民自由联盟]]表示将代表“公民支持特朗普”（Citizens for Trump）和“组织俄亥俄”（Organize Ohio）发起法律诉讼，称抗议活动许可迟迟不下发阻碍了抗议者的行动<ref name="TobiasACLU">{{cite news|last1=Tobias|first1=Andrew|title=ACLU threatens to sue Cleveland over delay in acting on demonstration permits for Republican National Convention|url=http://www.cleveland.com/rnc-2016/index.ssf/2016/05/aclu_threatens_to_sue_clevelan.html|accessdate=2016-05-22|work=[[The_Plain_Dealer|The Plain Dealer]]|date=2016-05-19|archive-date=2016-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160724113526/http://www.cleveland.com/rnc-2016/index.ssf/2016/05/aclu_threatens_to_sue_clevelan.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年6月14日美国公民自由联盟正式在[[美国俄亥俄北区联邦地区法院|联邦地方法院]]提起诉讼<ref>{{cite news |last=DuVall |first=Eric |url=http://www.upi.com/Top_News/US/2016/06/17/ACLU-sues-Cleveland-over-GOP-convention-protest-restrictions/2391466190609/?spt=hs&or=tn_us |title=ACLU sues Cleveland over GOP convention protest restrictions |agency=United Press International |date=2016-06-14 |accessdate=2016-06-18 |archive-date=2016-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625060046/http://www.upi.com/Top_News/US/2016/06/17/ACLU-sues-Cleveland-over-GOP-convention-protest-restrictions/2391466190609/?spt=hs&or=tn_us |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 出席者与不出席者 ===
在特朗普越来越接近获得提名人身份的过程中，一些共和党大佬宣布不会出席党代会<ref name="RajuWalsh">Manu Raju & Deirdre Walsh,  [http://www.cnn.com/2016/04/12/politics/republican-convention-2016/ First on CNN: Top Republicans may skip GOP convention] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/04/12/politics/republican-convention-2016/ |date=20160808041515 }}, CNN (April 12, 2016).</ref><ref name="Peters">Jeremy W. Peters, [http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/02/us/politics/donald-trump-republican-convention.html 'I Can Watch It on TV': Excuses for Republicans Skipping a Donald Trump Convention] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/02/us/politics/donald-trump-republican-convention.html |date=20160716031517 }}, ''The New York Times'' (June 1, 2016).</ref>。仍在世的前几次大选共和党总统候选人中，只有1996年大选提名人[[鲍勃·多尔|鲍勃·多尔]]宣布会参加党代会；米特·罗姆尼（2012年）、[[约翰·麦凯恩|约翰·麦凯恩]]（2008年）、[[乔治·沃克·布什|乔治·沃克·布什]]（2004年和2000年）、[[乔治·赫伯特·沃克·布什|乔治·赫伯特·沃克·布什]]（1988年和1992年）均表示不会出席大会<ref>Shushannah Walshe & Alexander Mallin, [http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/gop-nominee-skip-republican-national-convention/story?id=38904356 All But One Former GOP Nominee to Skip Republican National Convention] {{Wayback|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/gop-nominee-skip-republican-national-convention/story?id=38904356 |date=20160805135744 }}, ABC News (May 5, 2016).</ref>。还有一些[[州长_(美国)|州长]]、[[美国众议院|众议院代表]]和[[美国参议院|参议员]]，尤其是面临竞争激烈的选举的那些，也表明不会参加大会，以远离特朗普及更专注于选区内的选民<ref name="RajuWalsh"/>。黨代表大會所在地俄亥俄、俄亥俄州州长凯西克没有参加大会，而代表俄亥俄的参议员[[罗伯·波特曼|罗伯·波特曼]]参加了大会，不过没有担任主要角色<ref name="aroarty">{{cite news|last1=Roarty|first1=Alex|title=At RNC, Portman Keeps Trump at a Distance|url=http://www.rollcall.com/news/politics/rnc-portman-keeps-trump-distance|accessdate=2016-07-20|publisher=Roll Call|date=2016-07-19|archive-date=2016-08-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817013957/http://www.rollcall.com/news/politics/rnc-portman-keeps-trump-distance|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年7月8日，[[内布拉斯加州|内布拉斯加州]]参议员[[本·萨斯|本·萨斯]]宣布不会出席大会<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usnews.com/news/articles/2016-07-08/nebraska-sen-ben-sasse-will-take-his-kids-to-watch-some-dumpster-fires-instead-of-attending-gop-convention|title=Nebraska Senator Will 'Take His Kids to Watch Some Dumpster Fires' Instead of Attending GOP Convention|access-date=2016-07-08|archive-date=2016-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816184022/http://www.usnews.com/news/articles/2016-07-08/nebraska-sen-ben-sasse-will-take-his-kids-to-watch-some-dumpster-fires-instead-of-attending-gop-convention|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其他不参会的参议员包括[[史蒂夫·戴恩斯|史蒂夫·戴恩斯]]（[[蒙大拿州|蒙大拿州]]）、[[杰夫·弗雷克|杰夫·弗雷克]]（[[亚利桑那州|亚利桑那州]]）和[[丽萨·穆尔科斯基|丽萨·穆尔科斯基]]（[[阿拉斯加州|阿拉斯加州]]）<ref name="WarnerJalonickAP">{{cite web|first1=Erica|last1=Werner|first2=Mary Clare|last2=Jalonick|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/caad6da7881a478c96820ca4aaea42e3/large-number-gop-senators-skipping-trumps-convention|title=Large number of GOP senators skipping Trump's convention|agency=Associated Press|language=en-US|access-date=2016-07-14|archive-date=2016-07-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160715175321/http://www.bigstory.ap.org/article/caad6da7881a478c96820ca4aaea42e3/large-number-gop-senators-skipping-trumps-convention|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

一些企业，包括[[可口可乐|可口可乐]]、[[微软|微软]]和[[惠普|惠普]]缩减了参会规模并减少了对党代会活动的捐助<ref name="Peters"/><ref>Jonathan Martin & Maggie Haberman, [http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/31/us/politics/donald-trump-republican-national-convention.html Corporations Grow Nervous About Participating in Republican Convention] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/31/us/politics/donald-trump-republican-national-convention.html |date=20160725190237 }}, ''The New York Times'' (March 30, 2016).</ref>。2016年6月，[[富国银行集团|富国银行集团]]、[[UPS|UPS]]、[[摩托罗拉|摩托罗拉]]、[[摩根斯坦利|摩根斯坦利]]、[[福特|福特]]和{{link-en|沃尔格林博姿联合公司|Walgreens Boots Alliance|沃尔格林博姿}}等六个资助了2012年党代会的公司宣布不会资助2016年的本次党代会<ref>Zachary Mider & Elizabeth Dexheimer, [http://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2016-06-16/more-companies-opt-to-sit-out-trump-s-coronation-in-cleveland More Companies Opt to Sit Out Trump's Coronation in Cleveland] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2016-06-16/more-companies-opt-to-sit-out-trump-s-coronation-in-cleveland |date=20160731043249 }}, Bloomberg Politics (June 16, 2016).</ref>。[[苹果公司|苹果公司]]随后也表示鉴于特朗普在某些选举议题上的立场，将撤回对党代会的资助<ref>{{cite web|title=Apple Won’t Be Funding The Republican Convention Because Of Trump|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/davidmack/apple-wont-be-funding-the-republican-convention|publisher=Buzzfeed News|accessdate=2016-06-19|archive-date=2016-08-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803161125/https://www.buzzfeed.com/davidmack/apple-wont-be-funding-the-republican-convention|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 座位安排 ===
大会开始两天前的7月16日，各州及美国各属地代表的座位安排公布<ref>Sara Pompeo, [http://wkbn.com/2016/07/16/2016-rnc-announces-delegation-seating-arrangement/ 2016 RNC announces delegation seating arrangement] {{Wayback|url=http://wkbn.com/2016/07/16/2016-rnc-announces-delegation-seating-arrangement/ |date=20160809035308 }}, [[WKBN-TV|WKBN]] (July 16, 2016).</ref><ref>[http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/2016-gop-convention-announces-the-delegation-seating-arrangement-300299694.html 2016 GOP Convention Announces the Delegation Seating Arrangement] {{Wayback|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/2016-gop-convention-announces-the-delegation-seating-arrangement-300299694.html |date=20160819080614 }} (press release), 2016 Republican National Convention (July 16, 2016).</ref>。俄亥俄州和得克萨斯州的代表座位被安排到了最后面，这被视为因这些州在初选中没有支持特朗普（俄亥俄州和得克萨斯州初选得票率最高的分别是凯西克和克鲁兹）而对代表施加的惩罚<ref>Robert Wang, [http://www.indeonline.com/news/20160717/rnc-notebook-creighton-sees-ohios-seating-as-punishment RNC notebook: Creighton sees Ohio's seating as 'punishment'] {{Wayback|url=http://www.indeonline.com/news/20160717/rnc-notebook-creighton-sees-ohios-seating-as-punishment |date=20160820163557 }}, ''[[Massillon_Independent|Massillon Independent]]'' (July 17, 2016).</ref><ref>Todd J. Gillman & Gromer Jeffers Jr., [http://www.dallasnews.com/news/politics/headlines/20160716-payback-time-for-texas-huge-gop-delegation-gets-distant-seats-at-trump-convention.ece Payback time for Texas? Huge GOP delegation gets distant seats at Trump convention] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dallasnews.com/news/politics/headlines/20160716-payback-time-for-texas-huge-gop-delegation-gets-distant-seats-at-trump-convention.ece |date=20160816233129 }} (July 16, 2016).</ref>。

== 大会委员会 ==
根据共和党规定，本次党代会共设四个委员会，在党代会开幕前为特定目的会面<ref>{{cite web |url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/prod-static-ngop-pbl/docs/Rules_of_the_Republican+Party_FINAL_S14090314.pdf |title=The Rules of the Republican Party |page=21 |format=PDF |orig-year=August 27, 2012 |date=2014-08-08 |accessdate=2016-07-18 |archive-date=2016-07-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716170734/https://s3.amazonaws.com/prod-static-ngop-pbl/docs/Rules_of_the_Republican%20Party_FINAL_S14090314.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。每个委员会由分别来自美国50个州、5个属地和[[哥伦比亚特区|哥伦比亚特区]]的一男一女共112人组成，这些成员由上述地区的56个代表团选出，每个代表团自行确定流程<ref name="OKeefeRelease">{{cite news|last1='Keefe|first1=Eric|title=Release the GOP Delegates|url=http://www.wsj.com/articles/release-the-gop-delegates-1465769777|accessdate=2016-06-20|newspaper=The Wall Street Journal|date=2016-06-13|archive-date=2016-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160812231536/http://www.wsj.com/articles/release-the-gop-delegates-1465769777|dead-url=no}}</ref>。党代会开幕前一周，每个委员会分别在克利夫兰的亨廷顿会议中心（Huntington Convention Center）会面<ref name="TroyToledoBlade">Tom Troy, [http://www.toledoblade.com/Politics/2016/07/13/GOP-platform-panel-nixes-LGBT-reference.html GOP platform panel nixes LGBT reference: Complete text of document kept under wraps] {{Wayback|url=http://www.toledoblade.com/Politics/2016/07/13/GOP-platform-panel-nixes-LGBT-reference.html |date=20160814054737 }}, ''Toledo Blade'' (July 13, 2016).</ref>。

=== 规则和议程委员会 ===
规则和议程委员会（Committee on Rules and Order of Business），或称规则委员会（Rules Committee），负责制定党代会的规则和直到下次党代会之前共和党遵循的规定，于7月14日会面。该委员会通过的规定必须经整个党代会采用才能生效。一般认为，规则委员会是权力最大的委员会。<ref>Kyle Cheney, [http://www.cnn.com/2016/04/12/politics/gop-convention-rules-committee/ Meet the Rules Committee: 112 people who may decide the Republican nominee] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/04/12/politics/gop-convention-rules-committee/ |date=20160808152959 }}, CNN (March 14, 2016).</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=RNC Rules Committee, 2016|url=https://ballotpedia.org/RNC_Rules_Committee,_2016|publisher=Ballotpedia|accessdate=2016-06-21|archive-date=2016-09-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914024053/https://ballotpedia.org/RNC_Rules_Committee,_2016|dead-url=no}}</ref>规则委员会主席是来自[[犹他州|犹他州]]的{{link-en|伊妮德·米克尔森|Enid Mickelsen}}和来自[[马萨诸塞州|马萨诸塞州]]的罗恩·考夫曼<ref>Tal Kopan, [http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/24/politics/rnc-rules-committee-membership/ RNC Rules Committee stocked with stalwarts] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/24/politics/rnc-rules-committee-membership/ |date=20160802151444 }}, CNN (June 24, 2016).</ref>。

2016年6月，{{link-en|埃里克·奥基夫 (政治活动家)|Eric O'Keefe (political activist)|埃里克·奥基夫}}和戴恩·沃特斯组建了一个名为{{link-en|不受束缚代表|Delegates Unbound}}（Delegates Unbound）的组织，根据CNN的报道，该组织尝试说服代表们他们有权力和能力给他们想要的人投票<ref>{{cite news|last1=LoBianco|first1=Tom|last2=Kopan|first2=Tal|title=RNC delegates launch 'Anybody but Trump' drive|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/17/politics/delegate-unbinding-effort-organized/|accessdate=2016-06-18|publisher=CNN|date=2016-06-17|archive-date=2016-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618133624/https://www.cnn.com/2016/06/17/politics/delegate-unbinding-effort-organized|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Bash|first1=Dana|last2=Raju|first2=Manu|title=How the GOP could cut ties with Donald Trump|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/16/politics/donald-trump-republican-anxiety/index.html|accessdate=2016-06-18|publisher=CNN|date=2016-06-17|archive-date=2016-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617221422/http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/16/politics/donald-trump-republican-anxiety/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=O'Keefe|first1=Eric|last2=Rivkin|first2=David|title=Release the GOP Delegates|url=http://www.wsj.com/articles/release-the-gop-delegates-1465769777|accessdate=2016-06-18|work=The Wall Street Journal|date=2016-06-13|archive-date=2016-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160812231536/http://www.wsj.com/articles/release-the-gop-delegates-1465769777|dead-url=no}}</ref>。大会代表坎达尔·安鲁也尝试说服其他代表更改大会规则，加入一个“良心条款”以便受（初选结果）束缚必须支持特朗普的代表可以投票反对他<ref>{{cite news|last1=Jaffe|first1=Alexandra|title=Campaign to Dump Trump at Republican Convention Emerges|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2016-election/campaign-dump-trump-republican-convention-emerges-n594766|accessdate=2016-06-18|publisher=NBC News|date=2016-06-17|archive-date=2016-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617231059/http://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2016-election/campaign-dump-trump-republican-convention-emerges-n594766|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年7月14日，规则委员会在连续15小时的马拉松式会议后，以84票对21票否决了向大会递交允许解放代表的“少数派报告”，从而为特朗普获得提名铺平道路<ref>{{cite web|first=Scott|last=Detrow|url=http://www.npr.org/2016/07/15/486153506/never-trump-is-nevermore-anti-trump-forces-fail-to-force-rnc-floor-fight|title='Never Trump Is Nevermore': Anti-Trump Forces Fail To Force RNC Floor Fight|publisher=NPR|accessdate=2016-07-17|archive-date=2016-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814083658/http://www.npr.org/2016/07/15/486153506/never-trump-is-nevermore-anti-trump-forces-fail-to-force-rnc-floor-fight|dead-url=no}}</ref>。规则委员会还一致通过更改40(b)规则，这个颇具争议的规则原本要求候选人必须在八个州得票领先才能有机会在党代会上获得提名，修改后只需五个州即可<ref name="PutnamRulesCmte">Josh Putnam, [https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2016/07/17/how-the-republican-party-made-it-harder-for-convention-delegates-to-vote-against-trump/ How the Republican Party made it harder for convention delegates to vote against Trump] {{Wayback|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2016/07/17/how-the-republican-party-made-it-harder-for-convention-delegates-to-vote-against-trump/ |date=20160822084803 }}, ''The Washington Post'' (July 17, 2016).</ref>。

=== 政纲委员会 ===
政纲委员会（Platform Committee）负责提出[[政纲|政纲]]草案，其拟出的草案必须经党代会批准生效<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rollcall.com/news/politics/heres-another-possible-headache-gop-convention|title=Here's Another Possible Headache at the GOP Convention|date=2016-04-13|newspaper=Roll Call|accessdate=2016-07-17|archive-date=2016-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820211307/http://www.rollcall.com/news/politics/heres-another-possible-headache-gop-convention|dead-url=no}}</ref>，委员会于7月11日和12日进行两天的公开听证<ref name="TroyToledoBlade"/><ref>Igor Bobic, [http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/gop-platform-lgbt-drama_us_57853c4ee4b07c356cfec2df Fight Over LGBT Rights Spawns Last-Minute Drama At GOP Platform Committee] {{Wayback|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/gop-platform-lgbt-drama_us_57853c4ee4b07c356cfec2df |date=20160718234214 }}, ''The Huffington Post'' (July 12, 2016).</ref>。政纲委员会的主席是[[怀俄明州|怀俄明州]]参议员[[约翰·巴拉索|约翰·巴拉索]]<ref>Daniel DiSalvo & James W. Ceaser, [http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2016/07/party-platform-national-convention/491147/ Do Party Platforms Still Matter?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2016/07/party-platform-national-convention/491147/ |date=20160811140854 }}, ''The Atlantic'' (July 13, 2016).</ref>。为讨论政纲相关事宜，共和党全国委员会组织了多达十场闭门会议，参会者包括企业游说者和官员，来自[[美国石油学会|美国石油学会]]、{{link-en|爱迪生电气学会|Edison Electric Institute}}、{{link-en|全国制造商协会|National Association of Manufacturers}}、[[哈德逊研究所|哈德逊研究所]]、{{link-en|能源研究协会|Institute for Energy Research}}和{{link-en|美国健康保险计划|America's Health Insurance Plans}}等<ref name="RestucciaTomm">Andrew Restuccia & Tony Romm, [http://www.politico.com/story/2016/06/donald-trump-republican-party-platform-223901 RNC taps groups reviled by Trump to write GOP platform] {{Wayback|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2016/06/donald-trump-republican-party-platform-223901 |date=20160808215013 }}, ''Politico'' (June 4, 2016).</ref>。

=== 资格委员会 ===
资格委员会（Credentials Committee）负责处理有关大会代表资格的纠纷，评估受到质疑的代表，以及有代表确定取消资格时提供替代人选建议<ref>Frank Lockwood, [http://www.nwaonline.com/news/2016/jun/10/webb-picked-for-gop-s-credentials-commi/ Wood picked for GOP's credentials committee] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nwaonline.com/news/2016/jun/10/webb-picked-for-gop-s-credentials-commi/ |date=20160808180410 }}, ''Northwest Arkansas Democrat Gazette'' (June 10, 2016) ("A Republican National Committee official has compared the contests committee to a trial court and the credentials committee to an appeals court.").</ref><ref>Rebecca Berg, [http://www.realclearpolitics.com/articles/2016/05/02/obscure_panel_may_have_big_effect_on_gop_convention_130442.html Obscure Panel May Have Big Effect on GOP Convention] {{Wayback|url=http://www.realclearpolitics.com/articles/2016/05/02/obscure_panel_may_have_big_effect_on_gop_convention_130442.html |date=20160505145043 }}, ''RealClearPolitics'' (May 2, 2016) (The RNC Committee on Contests ... will evaluate challenges to convention delegates selected at the state level, with the power to recommend that delegates be de-certified by the convention Committee on Credentials.").</ref>。委员会主席是前共和党全国委员会主席{{link-en|麦克·邓肯|Mike Duncan}}和{{link-en|阿肯色州共和党|Republican Party of Arkansas}}主席道尔·韦伯<ref>[https://www.gop.com/rnc-announces-credentials-committee-leadership/ RNC Announces Credentials Committee Leadership] {{Wayback|url=https://www.gop.com/rnc-announces-credentials-committee-leadership/ |date=20160920033739 }} (press release), 2016 Republican National Convention (June 3, 2016).</ref>。

=== 筹备委员会 ===
筹备委员会（Committee on Arrangements）负责安排大会日程和后勤工作<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.2016cle.com/community-updates/getting-to-know-the-committee-on-arrangements |title=Getting to Know the Committee on Arrangements |publisher=Cleveland2016 |accessdate=2016-07-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160927191538/https://www.2016cle.com/community-updates/getting-to-know-the-committee-on-arrangements |archive-date=2016-09-27 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，主席是前{{link-en|威斯康辛州共和党|Republican Party of Wisconsin}}主席史蒂夫·金<ref>Craig Gilbert, [http://www.jsonline.com/news/statepolitics/cleveland-gop-convention-will-have-very-wisconsin-flavor-b99761338z1-386687091.html Cleveland GOP convention will have very Wisconsin flavor] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jsonline.com/news/statepolitics/cleveland-gop-convention-will-have-very-wisconsin-flavor-b99761338z1-386687091.html |date=20160716011117 }}, ''Milwaukee Journal Sentinel'' (July 13, 2016).</ref>。

